Ascena Retail Group, Inc. (ASNA) Stake Increased by BlueCrest Capital Management Ltd




				 24 July, 2017,  16:57 | Author: Terri Saunders			













Sanders Morris Harris Inc. bought a new position in Ascena Retail Group during the first quarter valued at approximately $1,208,000. (NASDAQ:ASNA) recently saw its volume around 1.72 million shares and on average it trades 3.7 million shares a day. The firm owned 97,120 shares of the specialty retailer's stock after buying an additional 5,680 shares during the period. BlueCrest Capital Management Ltd's holdings in Ascena Retail Group were worth $155,000 as of its most recent SEC filing.A number of other institutional investors have also added to or reduced their stakes in ASNA. Thrivent Financial for Lutherans raised its position in Ascena Retail Group by 245.8% in the fourth quarter. Tudor Investment Corp ET AL now owns 106,800 shares of the specialty retailer's stock valued at $455,000 after buying an additional 49,072 shares in the last quarter. Teachers Retirement System of The State of Kentucky now owns 57,300 shares of the specialty retailer's stock worth $355,000 after buying an additional 32,208 shares in the last quarter. Canada Pension Plan Investment Board raised its position in Ascena Retail Group by 247.3% in the first quarter. Guggenheim Capital LLC now owns 607,988 shares of the specialty retailer's stock worth $3,764,000 after buying an additional 405,687 shares during the period. Bank of Montreal Can boosted its position in shares of Ascena Retail Group by 6,135.7% in the first quarter. Finally, Highbridge Capital Management LLC raised its position in Ascena Retail Group by 13,454.5% in the fourth quarter. Acquires 37,760 Shares of Ascena Retail Group, Inc. Hedge funds and other institutional investors own 96.99% of the company's stock. (NASDAQ:ASNA) closed July 21 at $2.2, down -75.85% or $6.91 from its record high price of $9.11. Ascena Retail Grp Cmn (NASDAQ:ASNA) has a market cap of $468.52 Million and the number of outstanding shares have been calculated 199.37 Million. The share price has moved forward from its 20 days moving average, trading 